    "short_description": {
        "value": "SSL4EO-S12 is a large-scale, globally distributed, multi-temporal and multi-sensor dataset for self-supervised learning in Earth observation. It provides 251,079 locations worldwide, each with Sentinel-1 dual-pol SAR, Sentinel-2 L1C (top-of-atmosphere) and L2A (surface reflectance) multispectral images, sampled in four seasons (2020/2021), for a total of over 3 million 2640m x 2640m patches. The dataset is designed for unsupervised pre-training and benchmarking of self-supervised learning methods in remote sensing.",
        "confidence": 0.7569
    },
